Edopoids include the Late Carboniferous genus Edops and the family Cochleosauridae . Dendrerpetontidae has also been included in Edopoidea , and is the oldest known temnospondyl family . Balanerpeton woodi is the oldest species , having been present in the Triassic period. Dendrerpetontids are known from fossils from the early Triassic to the late Permian period.

The evolution of the swimming apparatus in temnospondyls is another important factor in their classification. Dendrerpetontids have a free-swimming circulatory system , which may have been inherited from early tetrapod ancestors. However, the circulatory system of dendrerpetontids was later modified into a more specialized system in other temnospondyls.
